🔒 Task 5: Cybersecurity Awareness & Threat Mitigation
Role: Student Digital Ambassador

Objective: Identifying, analyzing, and neutralizing financial cyber threats in the Indian digital ecosystem.

📋 Overview
In an increasingly digitized academic environment, cybersecurity is a fundamental pillar of digital literacy. As the Student Digital Ambassador, I have developed this resource to address the rising tide of UPI and Online Payment Fraud. This task involves a critical analysis of social engineering tactics and the creation of a localized safety framework for the student community.

🔍 Part A: Case Study – The UPI "Request Money" Scam
This folder includes casestudy.md, a detailed 250-word analysis of QR code-based financial fraud.

The Crime: A social engineering attack where victims are tricked into entering their UPI PIN under the guise of receiving a "scholarship refund" or "prize."

Mechanism: Step-by-step breakdown of how scammers transition from a "Hook" (fake urgency) to the "Execution" (unauthorized debit).

Impact: Financial loss and the erosion of digital trust among students.

🛡️ Part B: 'Stay Safe Online' Checklist
The prevention-checklist.md file provides 8 actionable security measures specifically curated for college students in India.

Key Highlights: Strict UPI PIN protocols, Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) for social media, and verifying "HTTPS" on academic portals.

Reporting Channels: Includes the National Cyber Crime Portal (cybercrime.gov.in) and the 1930 Helpline for immediate incident reporting.

